verses.roman:
govinda-kāśīśvare prabhu kailā ājñāpana
'duṅhe anyatra māgi' kara udara bharaṇa'

synonyms: govinda-kāśīśvare—unto Govinda and Kāśīśvara; prabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; kailā—made; ājñāpana—order; duṅhe—both of you; anyatra—elsewhere; māgi'-begging; kara udara bharaṇa—fill your bellies.
translation: Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu ordered Govinda and Kāśīśvara,"You may both take alms elsewhere to fill your bellies."
